&lt;p&gt;Urgent Care Practitioner - The Haven&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A new and exciting opportunity has arisen in Coastal Urgent Care services for an enthusiastic and forward thinking Mental Health Practitioner. Applications are welcomed from qualified Mental Health Nurses, Social Workers and Occupational Therapists. As a service we are moving towards providing 24 hour/365 days acute community mental health support. Introducing new and flexible ways of working we aim to bring together acute community services and ensuring that service users are seen promptly and effective care planning is timely . The successful applicants will work under the umbrella of Urgent Care Services working primarily within the The Haven at Meadowfield. These posts are new and as such offer clinicians the opportunity to be central to the development of Urgent Care Services in Worthing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers The Trust&#39;s Golden Hello for band 5 or 6 Nurses, or a Relocation package up to a maximum of £2000. (pro rata applies and subject to terms and conditions. Please see attached Protocol document).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Gina Wilson&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address gina.wilson@sussexpartnership.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01903 843200&lt;/p&gt;
